I gotta admit this is pretty cool. I will say though the weirdest part about it for me was how the AI tried to show how I looked as an average size person with no Achondroplasia. 

What a world!

I’m humbled and honored to announce that I won the Best Lead Actor Award at the @theutahfilmfestival this evening.

What an experience and it’s just so surreal. I’m really proud of @the_binding_bell  and grateful that @jeremiahholt gave me a role that made me step out of my comfort zone. I got to watch the screening last night with my family and that was also super special. @jerilynnrogers I couldn’t have done this without you and hope everyone knows that she is a rockstar! 

I’ve learned a lot over the years with one thing being, never be afraid to put yourself out there. You really never know what will come of it. 

I also want to shout out @samuel.j.hart and the rest of the team at @byuadlab winning the Best Commercial Award! That was such a fun project so I’m stoked to see it being recognized!

My birthday is tomorrow so what a way to start 30!!!! ❤️

Episode 52 will host the amazing @lee_liston this one is a very fun and very interesting one! Can’t wait for you guys to watch it! Tune in every Saturday 9AM! #tinybutmighty #smallbutstrong #smallwonder

So there is a new FDA Drug circulating called Voxzogo. 

From Google “Voxzogo is a medicine for treating achondroplasia in patients aged 2 years and older whose bones are still growing. Achondroplasia is an inherited disease caused by a mutation (change) in a gene called fibroblast growth-factor receptor 3 (FGFR3).” 

I don’t agree that it’s a disease and honestly I haven’t really paid attention to how the existence of this drug has made me feel. 

Growing up there were a lot of times I didn’t want my Dwarfism. There were times I thought I was a monster because of all the pointing and staring. I hated it so much. 

Years later I’m so proud of it. It has given me so many unique opportunities and experiences. I’m grateful for my unique perspective and how this condition has allowed me to relate to others that I may not have been able to otherwise. 

I know that all things have their purpose and grateful that I was blessed with wonderful body.

Hey my friends!

A while back my friend Eric Taylor reached out to me and asked if he could do a documentary on my life with an emphasis on my pursuit of acting as a person with Dwarfism. Well I’m stoked to announce that the premiere is tomorrow 4/26/23! 

This is a first come first serve event so if you plan to be there let me know and be there right at 5:00pm when the doors open if you can! There are a lot of projects and I imagine a lot of people will be there. 

It will be showing in the second block. The first block will begin at 5:30pm and the second block will begin at 8:00pm. There will be a 30 minute intermission from 7:30-8:00pm.

If you’d like to go please let me know and I’ll forward you the invite email. The event will be at the Geneva Megaplex in Vineyard.

I’m really proud of this project and hope you can come!

*Please note that at least one project will be rated R in the lineup.

I’m so excited that I can finally share this with everyone. @damianthedayton reached out to me to do this awesome piece with the @creatably team for @coldcaseicecream ! I was beyond stoked to do this because I’ve never gotten to put this kind of energy into a commercial before. 

I also want to add that it was amazing getting to meet @tony_cox_mr_parker and @bradwilliamscomic ! Tony is a legend and has been in movies like Spaceballs, Willow, Beetlejuice, and Bad Santa! He was so nice to talk to and fun to get to know. It was seriously an honor! 

I know Se7en is a highly revered movie so I tried to give it my all! 

This was my first time getting to act with other people with Dwarfism so that was also really cool! 

I’m really proud of what the team accomplished and I hope you enjoy!!! (I’ll put the link in my bio!)

Happy Halloween everyone!

Back in 2018 I saw that @therock was creating a show called the @nbctitangames. At the time no one had any idea what it entailed but I knew I wanted to be a part of it. 

I started working out and training two times a day. My friend @devinsupertramp filmed my audition and I waited in anticipation. 

I didn’t get into the games but a friend of mine introduced me to @fitcon. There I met @calumvonmoger, @jaycutler, and a few other fitness legends. They encouraged me to body build so I decided to take a whack at it. 

I never competed but the experience of becoming fit and find a love of training changed my life. I am forever grateful that fitness came into my life.

A little throwback to one of the sadder moments of my life:

Too short to ride the cool kid rides at the theme parks and too tall to get free ice cream.

So close, yet so far.

Hey everyone for those of you that don’t know me, my name is Lee! I have a type of Dwarfism called Achondroplasia. Over the past 8 years I’ve had a chance to be a part of some amazing things as an actor and bodybuilder. 

I’ve worked with @gymshark, @evermorepark, @devinsupertramp, and many others. 

Now I want to start finding my voice on social media and especially talk about Dwarfism in general. Make sure to follow if you want to learn more and always feel free to ask questions!

Why having Dwarfism is like being born a celebrity. 

Now when I say celebrity I mean when it comes to how celebrities are treated in public. A lot of times going out in public means you’re going to get some unwanted attention. 

Truthfully it’s not always easy to handle. Sometimes you just want to go out and about without feeling like you need to educate someone.

What helps me a lot is wearing AirPods so it drowns out the noise around me. While this has always been nice, I want to do what I can to spread awareness and help people understand that people with Dwarfism are people just like anyone else. 

Let me know your thoughts, if you have anything to add, or just have any questions!

I’ll never forget what it was like getting my legs straightened after being bow legged. It was one of the hardest experiences of my life. I was nervous to get the surgery not knowing what it was going to be like after. 

I was in two casts for 8 weeks and had to learn to walk again because the muscles in my legs were gone. I had to go to endure lots of physical therapy and it was honestly sometimes a very lonely experience. 

I remember being asked if I would do the surgery again after everything was done and I initially said no. But over the years I’ve seen how it drastically changed the course of my life. 

I’ve loved sharing my experiences growing up with Dwarfism so far and I hope you’ve enjoyed the videos. Let me know if you have any questions and I hope you have a wonderful day!

The word midget has always been something that has bothered me. I hate when people say it because it feels like in that moment it’s all the person sees me as. 

I know some people with Dwarfism are okay with the word but I’m not. I think there are better things to call people with the number one being their name. 

When I talk to people I don’t say “Hey what should I call you?” I ask what their name is. 

I also want to point out that it’s something that people have not what they are. “They have Dwarfism.” It’s a condition and not someone’s whole identity. So if you’re ever wondering what to call someone with Dwarfism, why not call them by their name? And if you don’t know it. Ask. 

#dwarfismawareness #achondroplasie

When you have Dwarfism you usually know that it’s going to be hard find stuff that fits you. For clothes I go to the kids section since most adult clothing is too big. 

Now imagine this. You’re excited to ride a new ride at a local theme park but there’s no minimum height requirement on the ride. So you wonder if you’re tall enough with no way to know. So you get to the park and find out that you’re not tall enough.

Imagine how frustrating that would be to know that you have to guesstimate, hope for the best, and settle for whatever fits you. I don’t love all the clothes in the kids sections but I definitely settle on what fits. 

I would really love it if e-bikes had minimum height requirements so I knew from the get go if I could ride it without the trial and error. End of rant. 

#dwarfismawareness #ebikes #height #frustration

“When people take pictures or videos of me out in public it hurts because I feel like people think they are at a zoo. 

They aren’t at a zoo I am a human being.

I should be able to go throughout my daily life without the worry that someone will take picture or video of me without my permission.” - Lee Liston

#dwafism #dwarfismawareness

So a while back @damianthedayton at @creatably pitched this really cool idea to do a @coldcaseicecream commercial where we recreate a scene from the movie Se7en. 

It was a super awesome experience where I got to work with @tony_cox_mr_parker (Beetlejuice, Willow, Bad Santa, and Spaceballs to name a few) and  @bradwilliamscomic 

When I was asked to play “John Dough” I really wanted to commit to the look so I shaved my head. I was really nervous what my bald head would look like with my scars and shunt. It turned out awesome I loved it. 

It was such an awesome experience acting with actors at eye level, especially with a project like this. 

Make sure to check out the commercial if you haven’t!

Also a huge shout out to @mini_moustachery for doing such a great job with the haircut!

Also @marvelstudios if you’re looking for an actor to play Puck in the MCU! Let me know!

#dwarfismawareness #actor #newexperiences
